      • select

        public java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object>> select(java.lang.String[] columnNames,
                                                                                                       java.lang.String tableName,
                                                                                                       java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.String>[] innerJoins,
                                                                                                       java.lang.String where)
                                                                                                throws java.sql.SQLException
        Generates the SQL select statement text based on the given parameters and passes it to the DatabaseManager's executeSelect method along with the database URl and credentials
        Parameters:
        columnNames - The column names in the database table to be read
        tableName - The table to be read
        innerJoins - Data required to perform SQL inner joins to gather the correct data from the database. Contains the foreignKey, foreignTableName and localTableName used in "INNER JOIN foreignTableName ON localTableName.foreignKey = foreignTableName.foreignKey".
        where - the where part of the select statement, e.g. (vaccineID = 1)
        Returns:
        The data gathered from the SQL select command
        Throws:
        java.sql.SQLException
